This code will produce two diagrams side by side as shown in your image. The first diagram represents the graph for the sequence \(3^\ell 5^\ell 1^+\), and the second diagram shows the corresponding 3-line graph with the twist of the middle edge changed by \(-6\) from the case shown in Figure \ref{3-sph-graphs}. Adjust the `bend left=45` option if you need to modify the angle of the twist.

